# CLAUDE.md

This file provides guidance to Claude Code when working with code in this repository.

## Commands

```bash
# Setup
python -m venv .venv
pip install -r requirements-dev.txt

# Run app
python -m {{ repo_name.replace('-', '_') }}.main

# Lint and format
ruff check .
ruff format .

# Type check
mypy {{ repo_name.replace('-', '_') }}/

# Tests
pytest

# Pre-commit
pre-commit run --all-files
pre-commit install
```

---

## Architecture

```
{{ repo_name.replace('-', '_') }}/core/      # All business logic — no UI here
{{ repo_name.replace('-', '_') }}/ui/        # PySide6 only — calls core, contains no logic
templates/                                    # Jinja2 template files for scaffold output
tests/                                        # Tests against core only
```

Data flows one way: UI → config model → core logic → disk. Side effects run after core logic.

---

## Engineering principles

- UI stays thin. No branching logic, no file I/O in `{{ repo_name.replace('-', '_') }}/ui/`.
- Prefer config + templates over conditional generation logic.
- Generated output must be deterministic and easy to diff.
- Avoid over-abstracting v1. Three similar lines beat a premature helper.
- Side effects (git, external calls) live only in dedicated modules.

---

## Development workflow

Each ticket follows these phases. Use the corresponding slash command to enter each phase:

```
/groom-ticket WOR-123     # PO review: scope, acceptance criteria, splitting
                          # Linear: Backlog → Groomed

/start-ticket WOR-123     # PO + Architect: restate req, plan files/tests, create branch
                          # Linear: Groomed → ReadyForLocal

/implement-ticket WOR-123 # Local worker: reads manifest, implements within allowed_paths

/security-check           # bandit scan + OWASP diff review → PASS / WARNINGS / FAIL

/finalize-ticket          # Coverage check, docs update, PR creation
                          # Linear: InProgressLocal → MergedToEpic

/close-epic WOR-123       # When all sub-tickets are MergedToEpic: create epic → main PR
                          # Linear: epic → MainPRReady → Done
```

Command files live in `.claude/commands/`.

